          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1679397850750-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot over a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>garam masala</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for an initial 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[6 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong>, stir it all together and cook for a further 1-2 min – this is your <strong>masala sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1679397855215-x200.jpg",
